<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="374" pageId="3" pageNumber="373" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[491,1529,1754,2020]" lastBlockId="4.[491,1548,229,323]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="374" pageId="3" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[531,642,1927,1951]" pageId="3" pageNumber="373">Remarks</emphasis>
— Male and female are well-described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rosso de Ferradas, B." box="[1132,1435,1927,1951]" pageId="3" pageNumber="373" pagination="23 - 34" refId="ref8316" refString="Rosso de Ferradas, B. 2006 b. Arrenuridos de la cuenca del Rio Parana, Argentina (Acari: Parasitengona: Hydrachnidia). Rev. Soc. Ent. Argent., 65: 23 - 34." type="journal article" year="2006">Rosso de Ferradás (2006b)</bibRefCitation>
and therefore only some measurements are given and an illustration of the male dorsum is presented. The only difference with her illustration of the male is that the associated setae of Dgl-3 are located medially and distanced of these glandularia. The areas with finer porosity are not mentioned in the original description of K. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K." box="[1016,1160,264,288]" pageId="4" pageNumber="374" pagination="161 - 247" refId="ref8570" refString="Viets, K. 1954 b. Wassermilben aus dem Amazonasgebiet (Hydrachnellae, Acari). (Systematsche und okologische Untersuchungen). Bearbeitung der Sammlungen Dr. R. Braun, und Dr. H. Sioli, Belem. Schweiz. Zschr. Hydrol., 16: 78 - 151, 16: 161 - 247. doi: 10.1007 / BF 02483636" type="journal article" year="1954">Viets (1954b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
